On the topic of exporting tables... I would love it if there was a way to export tables to another portal
Would this be useful for “Normal” users? lol
Probably not, but I could say the same for the ability to export pages and modules to another portal
I have a few clients that have multiple portals for themselves, and this would be useful for those companies

I'm going to do some experimentation
So it's looking to me like the copy fails every time there is a HubDB dependancy.  When I comment out the code related to the HubDB, everything copies fine.
If this gets fixed, we don’t even need a “Copy to portal” on the HubDB side, since the references will just carry over and (ideally) create an identical table in the new portal
Does the portal you’re trying to copy to have the Website Package?
Definitely.  Both portals I've been trying to move modules between have the Website package

I agree that this would definitely fill the need for a copy to portal option in hubDB.  

It would also be a nice fix to have.  Instead of being able to simply copy over a module, I had to recreate the module and the HubDB table in the portal I was trying to move it to
